{
  "stem": "6924.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I guess we started, told me, with chicken soup.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And chicken, I mean, everything, I mean.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But that was usually our meat meal, because that was the Shabbat meal with challah, with everything, a Jewish meal.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My schooling, my father always believed in schooling.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And for Jewish people and Poland, it was very hard to get into a public school, so he sent me to a private school.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I finished the private school.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It's like a regular elementary school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then I attended a gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "There was a private gymnasium, because there was always a-- there was also a public gymnasium in our town with no charge.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But no Jews could have got into that school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The school had maybe 500 students, and I think they kept one or two Jewish students to show that there's no discrimination.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father sent me to a private gymnasium when I was 13, until I finished at school when I was 18.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Now, I also attended, in my younger years, when I was-- before I started public school, Hebrew preschool.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They call it Tarbut, what I attended.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Did you notice in your early-- in your schooling as a young boy anti-Semitism in the town?",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, yeah.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no question about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The first thing that you couldn't get into that-- that public gymnasium.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And they were just like better one, better people.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In school, we had-- our school had only Jewish-- was only Jewish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I wasn't in contact with any-- any Polacks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The only time that, you know, that you had to-- we always were aware they were Jewish, you know.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Like at nighttime, we walked at nighttime, but in the late '30s already you had to think about it.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It became dangerous to walk at nighttime.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
